Project Vera Rubin: Gravitational Lens Discovery EngineThis pipeline is designed to identify and vet galaxy-scale gravitational lenses in wide-field surveys (ZTF/Rubin).🔭 MethodologyAnchor Selection: 100k+ seeds from Quasar/AGN catalogs.Time-Delay Analysis: Z-transformed Discrete Correlation Function (ZDCF) for lag detection.Astrometric Vetting: Local Gaia DR3 star-masking to eliminate foreground interlopers.Mass Modeling: Singular Isothermal Sphere (SIS) mass estimation from Einstein Radii.Spectroscopic Validation: Automatic cross-matching with DESI Target IDs and redshifts.📊 Current StatusVetting Complete: 7 High-Probability Candidates (The "Magnificent Seven").Mass Leader: WISEA J003903.93+242208.4 ($1.57 \times 10^{11} M_\odot$).Confirmation: DESI Target ID 39628354311163326 (ZWARN=0).4. License SelectionChoose the MIT License. It is the standard for open-source academic code, allowing others to use and build upon your pipeline while protecting your original work as the author.Next Step for Project Vera RubinOnce the repository is created, your first "Push" should include the Gaia Local Mirror script we discussed. This solidifies your transition to a professional, offline-capable workstation in Battle Creek.